{ White clearly has a nice attacking position, while Black doesn't seem to have anything going for him at all (where is his counterplay?) . In the actual game, White got a little excited and tried for instant gratification with [%mdl 32768] Threatening 2. f5 Since we know that the Knight's position should be improved, and since we know that e4 is the Promised Land, the only question that remains is 'how do we get it there?' The answer doesn't call for any calculation at all: 1. Nc3 with Ne4 to follow. }
( { For those wondering what happens if Black whacks the Knight off after }
1.Nc3 { with Ne4 to follow. } 1...Bb7 2.Ne4 Bxe4 3.dxe4 Rg8
