{ Another form of Knight domination is the dreaded 'entombed piece.' This is a situation where a Knight (or Bishop!) is stuck in a cage of pawns. [%mdl 32768] This creates an obvious attack on the f3-Knight. That should be easy to deal with, but it turns out to be a clean winner for Black. }
2.Ng1 ( 
{ Since e5 and g5 are off limits, that only leaves this retreat to g1 or
the material-losing hop to h4: } 2.Nh4 Bxh4 3.gxh4 Qxh4
{ with an extra pawn and a strong attack. } ) 2...f3 $1
