1.Qe4
{ [%mdl 32768] A common but important idea. The Queen uses its light-squared Bishop to set up a catapult (usually referred to as a 'battery,' but that term reminds me of a marital debacle so I try to avoid it) that will throw it deep (and decisively) into the enemy position (in this case, on h7). This is also known as 'riding the Bishop's vapors.' }
1...f5 ( { There's no salvation in } 1...g6 2.Bxh6 Nxe5
{ Black was lost in any case, but this makes a bad situation worse because
after } 3.Qxb7 Nxd3 4.Qa6 Nb2 5.Bxf8 Bxf8 6.Rfb1
{ he loses the Knight and leaves White with an extra Rook. } ) 2.exf6 Rxf6
3.Re1 Na5 ( 
{ There's no real defense. Trying to hold onto e6 falls on its face after }
3...Qd7 4.Qh7+ Kf7 5.Bg5 $1 hxg5 { 5...Rxf3 6.Bg6+ Kf8 7.Qh8 } 6.Nxg5+ Ke8
7.Qg8+ { and now } 7...Rf8
{ 7...Bf8 8.Nxe6 makes the last line look like a mercy killing. } 8.Nxe6 Rxg8
9.Bg6# { would make Black's toes curl. } ) 4.Qh7+ Kf7 5.Bg5 $1
{ And now Black has nothing better than ...Qg8. } 5...Qg8 ( 5...hxg5 6.Nxg5+
Ke8 7.Nxe6 Rxe6 8.Qg8+ Kd7 9.Qxe6+ Kc7 10.Qxe7+ { offers no hope at all. } )
6.Bxf6 Qxh7 7.Bxh7 Bxf6 8.Be4
{ And Black doesn't have enough compensation for the lost Exchange. } *

