{ In our last example, White had the two Bishops, but the dark-squared
Bishop was the hero since it not only found a home on a very long and clear
diagonal, but there was nothing in Black's camp that could oppose it. This same idea comes to the fore when contemplating the intricacies of
Bishop vs. Knight. If the Knight hasn't found some god-like support point, and if the Bishop finds a clear diagonal, then the Knight will often be at a disadvantage. }
