15.Bxc6 Rc8! 16.d5 Be5 16...Nb8!? 17.Bb7 Bxd5 18.Bxc8 Qxc8 19.Rac1 Na6 also
gives Black a small edge. 17.dxe6 Nb8 18.Rad1 Qe7 19.Qxf5 Nxc6 20.exf7+ Qxf7 21.Qxf7+ Rxf7 when Black's extra piece has to be more important than
White's three pawns. } 14...Qxd7 15.Nc1 Bd6 16.Nd3
{ both this and 14. Nd3 leave White with all the play thanks to the factors
mentioned earlier. } ) ( 13...Qe7 14.Nd3 Rad8 15.b4
