{ Level: 1400-1800. } 15.Bg5 $1
{ [%mdl 32768] White plays directly for a superior Knight vs. Bishop position, which would also create a permanent grip on d5. This move is both thematic and easy to understand: Black's Knights are the guardians of d5, while White's Bishop will never be able to directly affect that square. Thus, White wants to swap off both black Knights, leaving him with a dark squared Bishop vs. (ideally) a white Knight lording over the board on d5. }
15...Rfc8 16.Nh2
{ It's important that you appreciate how this maneuver turns a once lazy
Knight into an active participant in the battle for d5. } *

