{ [%mdl 32768] Yes, White might well have an edge if he could retain his Bishops, but there was no way to stop Black from using our basic anti-two Bishops plan of trading off one of the Bs. In this case, Black would achieve it by ...Nfd5 followed by ...Bf4. Explaining the Rating Spread The idea of trading off one of the enemy Bishops if the opponent has two of them is something a 1400 player can understand and use. }
