to play in such situations: one is to accept that you're worse and just improve your game bit by bit in an effort to steer the position to eventual equality and a draw. The other is to seek tactical chances, remembering that you can't force such things since overaggressive moves tend to create
self-inflicted weaknesses and can make things worse. } 26...g5 $6
{ The idea is to crack e4 with ...g5-g4. However, the poor placement of the
