@@StartFEN@@2r5/pp3p2/3n1k1p/P2p1p1P/3P1K2/3BPP2/1P6/6R1 b - - 0 29@@EndFEN@@ 29...Rc7 then 30.Rg8 is very strong, and finally, if
@@StartFEN@@2r5/pp3p2/3n1k1p/P2p1p1P/3P1K2/3BPP2/1P6/6R1 b - - 0 29@@EndFEN@@ 29...Ke6 (as played in the game), then 30.Rg7 adds to Black's woes. This means that, like it or not, @@StartFEN@@2r5/pp3p2/3n1k1p/P2p1p1P/3P1K2/3BPP2/1P6/6R1 b - - 0 29@@EndFEN@@ 29...a6! (even though
