{ Material sacrifices that create a 'battle of the imbalances' are
commonplace in virtually every opening. An excellent example of this is the
highly popular Marshall Attack, which sees Black offering a pawn for a lead in development, active pieces, a slight weakening of the light
squares in white's kingside, and good dynamic chances. On the other hand, White has a solid position and an extra pawn. }
