Qg6 { 6...Nxd4 7.Nxd4 exd4 8.Bf4 is strong for White. } 7.Be2 Qxe4 8.Ng5 Qxg2
9.Bf3 { and Black's Queen is a goner. } ) ( { • } 5...Nce7 6.c5 $1
{ Forcing Black's Queen onto a more vulnerable square. } 6...Qxc5 7.d4 exd4
8.b4 { and the game is over: } 8...Qc6 9.Bb5 Qd6 10.Bf4 Qg6 11.Nxc7+ { etc. }
) ( { • } 5...Nce7 6.c5 $1 Qc6 7.d4
{ Freeing the c1-h6 diagonal for the dark-squared Bishop with gain of time.
7.Bb5! since 7...Qxb5? 8.Nxc7+ picks up the Queen. } 7...exd4 8.b4 Qg6
9.Nxc7+ ) 6.d4 Nf6 ( 6...exd4 $2 7.Bf4 ) 7.c5 $1 bxc5 8.dxe5 $1 ( 
{ Even stronger than } 8.dxc5 { . } ) 8...Nxe5 9.Bf4 Nxd5 ( 9...Nxf3+ 10.gxf3
Qc6 11.Nxc7+ Kd8 12.Nxa8 Qxa8 13.Qa4 ) 10.Bxe5 Qb6 11.Qxd5
