can handle. Clearly, the robotic 9. a3, though a common idea in the English
Opening, wasn't right for this particular position. As should be evident, a fresh look can pay huge dividends. 

Although these last two examples showed how lazy thinking led to missed
dynamic and/or tactical possibilities, the same can be said about positional ideas. In the following game we witness a high-class example of a very astute chess outlook. }
