{ Level: 1800-2200. } 27...b4 $1
{ [%mdl 32768] A star move. Computers don't like it, but if Black's pawn can't move to b4 then his pieces will be doomed to eternal passivity. In that case Black would have to wait around and pray that White can't find a winning plan in the center or on the kingside. After the pawn sacrifice, Black's Bishop (which had Tall-Pawn status for most of the game) can enter the battle on b5 and his Rooks suddenly get use of the b-file. In other words, Black gets active pieces and a chance to fight! }
