opponent, the merrier the party will be. } 20.Bxh5 ( 
{ Desperation. The more 'reasonable' } 20.b3
{ leaves c3 very weak (the Rooks will eventually move to the c-file and
hunt it down) and also loses the h4-pawn to } 20...Bf6 ) 20...gxh5 ( 
{ According to Rybka, even stronger is } 20...Nc4 21.Rdf2 axb2 22.Bxg6 Rxa2
{ I have no doubt that it's right, but I can't criticize myself for
gobbling up a free piece! } ) 21.Nxh5 f6 22.b3 Kh7
{ And White didn't have anywhere near enough compensation for the
sacrificed piece. The rest wasn't that difficult. } 23.Nf3 Bh6 24.Nf4 Rg8
25.Qh3 Ng4 26.Nd4 Nxe3 27.Qxe3 e5 28.Nf5 Bxf5 29.exf5 Qc7 30.Qe2 Bxf4 31.Qh5+
