{ And Black has suddenly transformed the position and now has a lovely
game! His kingside pawn majority promises him good chances against White's
King, and the hole on e5 is a marvelous home for Black's Knight, which rules the board from its new central perch. If that seemed a bit
complicated for some, let's demonstrate the old 'I'm going to make that square mine' mentality with a simpler example. }
