{ Of course, a weak square isn't just an ideal home for a Knight, other
pieces can also find that they are wonderfully placed there. 

Where is the black King's best square? The f3-pawn, being doubled, is
obviously weak but one might think it's safe enough since it's so deep in White's position while Black's Bishop is a dark-squared piece and thus can't attack it. However, f4 would be a lovely square for the King
since it's not only advanced but also bashing f3. Thus Black plays to get his King there. }
