far! } 16...Rc8 17.Bxa5 Qxa5+ 18.Kf2 Nf6 19.Qb3 Rc6
{ After 14. O-O, the rest of the game saw Black dominate c4, snuff out all
enemy counterplay, and infiltrate on the queenside and central light
squares. } ) 14...Qc7 15.Bg5 Rc8 16.f4 f6 17.Bh4 Qc4 18.Qe3 d5 19.e5 f5
20.Kh1 Qa4 21.h3 Qc2 22.Rfc1 Qe4 23.Qxe4 dxe4 24.d5
{ A desperate bid for activity. The idea of waiting around while the
a5-Knight made a home on c4 and the e8-Knight claimed d5 via ...Ne8-c7-d5
couldn't have appealed to him! } 24...exd5 25.Nd4 g6 26.Rab1 Nc7 27.Be7 Rfe8
28.Bb4 Nc4 29.Nc6 Ne6 $1
