gxf6
{ Black's position is hideous, but the opposite-colored Bishops makes
winning far from easy. } 16.Ke3 Bg6 17.Kd2
{ Using the King to take care of c4. However, 17. Nc3!? deserved serious
consideration. } 17...Be4 18.Bc1 Bg2 19.Kc3 Bf1 20.Bh6 Bg2 21.Bf4 Bf1 22.Nb2
Nc7 23.Nd1 Bg2 24.Ne3 Be4 25.Bh6 Ne8 26.Kd2 Nc7 27.Ke2 Ne8 28.Kf2 Nc7
{ White's been employing the usual Cat and Mouse strategy, hoping to wear
down the opponent. Now Kramnik points out that 28... Bb1!? followed by
