Bd3 34.Be7+ Kc7 35.Ne3 Kc8 36.Kg4 Kc7 37.Kh5 Ng7+ 38.Kh6 Ne8 39.h4 Kc8 40.h5
Kc7 41.Ng2 Kc8 ( 41...Bxc4 42.Kxh7 Bxd5 43.Nf4 Be4+ 44.Kg8 c4 45.Kf7 c3
46.Kxe8 c2 47.Bd8+ Kb8 48.Ne2 Bf3 49.Nc1 Bxh5+ 50.Ke7 { wins - Kramnik. } )
42.Nf4 Bc2 43.Ng6 $1
{ The correct move instead of the mistaken 43. Bxf6? (though White ended up
winning anyway). } 43...hxg6 44.hxg6 f5 ( 44...Bd3 45.g7 Nxg7 46.Kxg7 Bxc4
47.Bxf6 { is easy. } ) 45.g7 ( 45.Bxd6 { also does the job. } ) 45...Nxg7
46.Kxg7 Kc7 ( 46...Bd3 47.Bxd6 Bxc4 48.Bf4 Bxb5 49.Kf8 { is game over. } )
47.Bd8+ Kxd8 48.Kf8 { And White promotes his e-pawn. } 1-0

[Event "How to Reassess Your Chess "]
