{ We've seen the benefits that an advantage in space bestows upon its
owner. However, this doesn't mean that the spatially challenged player has
to roll over and die. In general, there are four ways to deal with space: 

- Exchange pieces so your limited territory is no longer uncomfortable. 

- Use pawn breaks to crack his seemingly indestructible pawn-façade. 

- Try and prove that your opponent's gain in space has left weak squares in
its wake. 

- Treat a space-gaining enemy pawn center as a target! } 1.--
{ [%mdl 32768] } *

