gives White nothing. 14...dxe4 15.Nd2 Nc5 16.Qe2 Qd3 17.Qxd3 17.Rae1 Qxe2 18.Rxe2 Bh5! 19.f3 exf3 20.Bxf3 Bxf3 21.Nxf3 Rad8 leaves Black with the better pawn structure. 17...Nxd3 18.Bd4 Rfd8 and Black has no problems. 13...Nxe5 14.dxe5 Bc5 15.Qe2 15.Nxe4 dxe4 16.Qe1 e3 17.fxe3 Qb6 18.Rd1 Rad8
19.Bd4 Bxd4 20.exd4 20.Rxd4 Rxd4 21.exd4 Qxd4+ 22.Qf2 Qxe5= 20...Bh5! 21.Rd2 Rxd4 22.Rxd4 Qxd4+ 23.Qf2 Qxf2+ 24.Rxf2 b6 25.Rd2 Rc8 26.Bh3 26.Rd7 Rc1+= 26...Rc1+ 27.Kf2 g5= 15...f5 16.exf6 Nxf6 17.Rad1 17.Qb5 Qd6 17...Kh8! 18.Nf3 Ne4 Black has a good, active position. }
