{ Black's position looks solid, but he's actually in terrible trouble. 

Explaining the Rating Spread I would expect a 1400 player that has carefully
read all the material in the Space section to appreciate White's enormous space advantage on the queenside. And, I would hope that he would want to
expand that spatial plus with the thematic 17. c5. However, it would probably take a higher-rated player to realize the true severity of Black's situation (after all, Black's position doesn't - visually - seem that bad!). Why are things so grim for Black? Because he doesn't have his usual kingside
counterplay and, without kingside chances, White's queenside attack will roll him off the board. }
