{ Level: 1800-2200. } 26.e5 $1
{ [%mdl 32768] Black had the initiative for the whole game, but suddenly White cashes in his fine static center for a host of dynamic considerations: 1) 26. e5 blocks Black's dark-squared Bishop; 2) It frees the e4-square for White's Knights and Bishop (thus the one pawn move activated three white minor pieces); 3) It intends to crack open the black King with moves such as e5-e6 or f4-f5. }
