has 'hole-like' qualities), the advance of the g-pawn is the only way to allow his forces to leap into action and begin a fight while Black's King still resides in the center. 

As always, it's important to decide if your position is dynamically or
statically inclined. If the answer is dynamic, then you have to play with all the energy you can muster, often sacrificing material and/or allowing weaknesses for fluid, active possibilities. }
